## LDAP (TCP 389 / 636)

### Discover the DC
```bash
nmap -p 389,636,3268,3269 192.168.1.10        # confirm DC: LDAP, LDAPS, Global Catalog ports
nslookup -type=SRV _ldap._tcp.corp.local      # locate DCs by name via DNS SRV record
```

### Test anonymous bind
```bash
ldapsearch -x -H ldap://192.168.1.10 -b "DC=corp,DC=local"   # query with no creds
# returns data = anonymous bind ENABLED (critical); error = disabled
```

### Authenticated reads (low-priv user is enough)
```bash
# All usernames
ldapsearch -x -H ldap://192.168.1.10 -D "cn=jdoe,cn=Users,dc=corp,dc=local" -w 'Spring2024' \
  -b "DC=corp,DC=local" "(objectClass=user)" sAMAccountName

# Password / lockout policy (know your safe limits before any cred testing)
ldapsearch -x -H ldap://192.168.1.10 -D "cn=jdoe,cn=Users,dc=corp,dc=local" -w 'Spring2024' \
  -b "DC=corp,DC=local" "(objectClass=domainDNS)" \
  lockoutThreshold lockoutDuration minPwdLength pwdProperties

# Domain Admins group members (high-value targets)
ldapsearch -x -H ldap://192.168.1.10 -D "cn=jdoe,cn=Users,dc=corp,dc=local" -w 'Spring2024' \
  -b "CN=Domain Admins,CN=Users,DC=corp,DC=local"

# Kerberoastable accounts (service accounts with an SPN)
ldapsearch -x -H ldap://192.168.1.10 -D "cn=jdoe,cn=Users,dc=corp,dc=local" -w 'Spring2024' \
  -b "DC=corp,DC=local" "(servicePrincipalName=*)" sAMAccountName servicePrincipalName
```

### Faster wrappers
```bash
windapsearch --dc-ip 192.168.1.10 -d corp.local -u jdoe -p Spring2024 --module users          # clean user table
windapsearch --dc-ip 192.168.1.10 -d corp.local -u jdoe -p Spring2024 --module domain-admins   # admins
SharpHound.exe --CollectionMethod All --Domain corp.local                                       # collect graph for BloodHound
```

### Flags
```
-x        simple auth          -b   base DN (where to search)
-H        LDAP URL/host        -D   bind DN (who you log in as)
-w        bind password        "(...)"   LDAP filter (what to match)
```

**Findings → next:** open 389 → bind → user list → policy → privileged accounts → SPNs / attack-path map.
**Enumeration stops at SPN discovery and BloodHound collection.** Cracking and path-walking are separate, in-scope phases.

