## When LDAP is blocked (port 389 firewalled)
```bash
rpcclient -U "" -N 192.168.1.10            # then: enumdomusers  (pull users over RPC 135/445)
crackmapexec smb 192.168.1.10 --users      # list users over SMB
kerbrute userenum -d corp.local --dc 192.168.1.10 users.txt   # validate usernames via Kerberos
dig axfr @192.168.1.10 corp.local          # DNS zone transfer (rare, but dumps records if allowed)
```

---

## Common ports
```
SNMP    161/udp                 LDAP   389/tcp        LDAPS  636/tcp
RPC     135/tcp                 SMB    445/tcp        GC     3268/3269/tcp
```

## Hardening (one-liners)
- **SNMP:** disable if unused · SNMPv3 (auth+encryption) · rotate community strings · restrict source IPs.
- **LDAP:** disable anonymous bind · enforce signing + channel binding · trim "Authenticated Users" reads · strong lockout policy · admins in Protected Users.
